cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper involves the development of a convolutional neural network (CNN) for classifying lesion malignancy in prostate cancer patients using multiparametric MRI. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also addresses the problem of small sample size, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging, which could place it in cs.MED (Medical Imaging) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
